formattedAddress: 4F, Mandarin Oriental Singapore (5 Raffles Ave, Marina Square)

tip.text: The fish & chips were great, but the real star? The mushy peas! So fresh! Bloody Mary good, but spicy! SUPER fast & attentive service. Definitely recommend.
Food lovers, unite! Bottom floor is full of cheeses, fresh meat and charcuterie. Head upstairs for a fab meal for lunch. Wash it down with a glass of Prosecco.
Pizza Napoli, the pork sandwich on the corner near the stairwell at I Tramezzini was amazing. €4 Prosecco with a generous pour make this the perfect stop.
Magnificent, authentic food & extremely attentive & helpful service. Goat with yoghurt, pork smoked with thyme & sage, & pork chops were all stunning. You must try this place!
Across the road from a great beach, this taverna had amazing service & very generous children's portions. The cherries, raki & lemoncello for afters were very welcome indeed.
Everything is fresh, delicious and flavourful. Make sure you leave room for dessert too (yoghurt panna cotta & chocolate mousse excellent). Service spectacular. Well worth a visit.
Brilliant service, fresh local food, delicious flavours. Make sure you stop here for dinner with a view. Rabbit was incredible, as was the sea bream, humus with apaki and humus with smoked eel.
Service was excellent. Our waiter happily adapting dishes for children. Delicious starters (shrimps, diablo), generous & delicious mains (tuna steak, big nose, & steak). Would return in a heartbeat.
Delicious homemade Cretan cuisine. Fresh local salad, melt in the mouth lamb, great stuffed vegetables - even the beef burger was full of herbs and tasted amazing. Worth a stop!
The duck confit was delicious, like all of the food our family of 4 ordered. The owner ensured we were well taken care of, accommodating our 2 children very well. Lovely food.
The marscapone cheesecake with berries was the best I have ever tasted. Light and fluffy. Perfection
The sous vide duck was as tender as anything. My 8 & 10 year old ate it all
Sea bass was delicate and delicious.
Fresh, seasonal & local offerings. Incredible flavours
Modern cuisine with only the freshest local produce is the speciality here. Knowledgeable & friendly waitstaff/sommelier help you make great choices. Incredible presentation & flavour. Must visit!
Oh man, the food here! Glorious. Great breakfasts with eggs etc. Eggs bene was lovely. Portobello was amazing. The sausage! Elderflower coffee was interesting too. Going in for cheesecakes now...
Love the Hangover Pizza. Blood orange soda also delish. Reasonable prices for tasty pizza. Some good vegetarian options too.
Loved the oyster selection & trying the range. Mon & Tue = $2 & $3 oysters. Worth a trip just for that! Burrata also incredible.
Incredible food, exquisitely cooked, every time. Current favs include beef marmalade with pickles, suckling pig, warm oysters, onglet steak, leeks with hazelnuts... The list goes on and on...

tip.text: I always make a point of bringing back some pork rillettes. Absolutely amazing.
Lovely bar, friendly service. Delicious Negroni.
Love the tomato on toast, the leeks with burnt butter & the delicious seafood. Will be back again.
Fantastic chef's table menu. Service excellent. They really know their stuff. Food exquisite. Not cheap, but worth every Penny.

tip.text: Friendly service, cheap beer and delicious wings. Try the Buffalo wings (mild was just right for me). Kids liked teriyaki wings but found the fries spicy.
Quite kid-friendly. Cuckoo clocks, colouring in & pork knuckles the size of your head!
We tried the spicy cream prawns, the mango bruschetta & the seafood pizza. All good options. Highlight was the mint burst (mojito-style) drink. Very refreshing.

tip.text: We ate grilled chicken banh mi, beef steak slices phở & lemongrass pork noodle. It was all delicious. Our kids loved the phở especially. We will be back!
Huge kids meal portions! Nutella milkshake craaaazy sweet. I much preferred the frozen mint lemonade.

tip.text: Book ahead for a seat as it fills up early. Delicious Teppan-Yaki. Kids menu is great - my two especially liked the beef. The prawns were amazing.
Chicken wings: simplicity itself, but oh so fab.
Pork neck. Oh yeah.
Another fav dish from the evening - Scallops.
Steak & "eggs". Don't miss it.
They have a seriously good banana lassi & the prawn & avocado salad is delish. Amazing value.
